---
description: Keep modules simple with minimal defensive checks and early exits
alwaysApply: true
---

# Simple Modules

Prefer straightforward module code that assumes valid internal contracts.

Avoid adding defensive checks for types, nil values, or instance existence when the calling path already guarantees them.

When code handles external or uncertain input boundaries, validation can still be useful.

## Prefer

```luau
local function applyJumpForce(character: Model, jumpForce: number)
	if jumpForce <= 0 then
		return
	end

	local rootPart = character.PrimaryPart
	rootPart:ApplyImpulse(Vector3.new(0, jumpForce, 0))
end
```

## Avoid

```luau
local function applyJumpForce(character: any, jumpForce: any)
	if typeof(character) ~= "Instance" then
		return
	end

	if not character then
		return
	end

	if typeof(jumpForce) ~= "number" then
		return
	end

	local rootPart = character and character.PrimaryPart
	if not rootPart then
		return
	end

	if rootPart:IsA("BasePart") then
		rootPart:ApplyImpulse(Vector3.new(0, jumpForce, 0))
	end
end
```

Use early exits (`return` / `continue`) to reduce nesting and keep the happy path easy to scan.

## Prefer

```luau
for _, simulation in simulations do
	if not simulation.Enabled then
		continue
	end

	if simulation.State == "Stopped" then
		continue
	end

	simulation:Step(deltaTime)
end
```

## Avoid

```luau
for _, simulation in simulations do
	if simulation.Enabled then
		if simulation.State ~= "Stopped" then
			simulation:Step(deltaTime)
		end
	end
end
```
